\f0\fs24 \'93Sorry,\'94 he said, returning his attention to the conversation. \'93I\'92m afraid I have an ulterior motive in attending this ball. I\'92m writing an article about Lord Connor.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Oh, really? On what subject?\'94 asked Grundy. \'93I\'92ve known Lord Connor a long time. Perhaps I could be useful.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Jonathan hesitated. He wanted to hear from Connor before saying anything more on the matter. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://5DC7FA61-36AD-4F54-A32D-336A1683E77A"}}{\fldrslt In fact}}, this was the first time he\'92d told anyone that he was writing about Connor. He thrust a hand into his pocket and felt a small scrap of paper in his father\'92s handwriting.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Jonathan was expected to take over his father\'92s duties at the publishing company. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://B91BCEFE-8812-431C-AEEC-7C0577A6CC43"}}{\fldrslt His office was still full of his father\'92s belongings, and Jonathan had been avoiding the task of cleaning it out ever since he\'92d returned to London.}} The truth was that he hadn\'92t taken the family business seriously for a long time. As a boy, he\'92d looked up to his father. He {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://836CFEDC-2C4A-468F-8E0D-5BF8D7BA6DB1"}}{\fldrslt wrote}} hundreds of articles and published them in his father\'92s paper, but Charles Grimmer had been so busy with running the company that he\'92d barely noticed Jonathan\'92s efforts. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://3F93C477-370C-48D3-9A83-CAC7B9DCDAA1"}}{\fldrslt Rather than continuing to fight for his father\'92s attention, Jonathan had turned his back on the family business.}}
\f1\fs20 \
