\f0\fs24 His father was an extensive note-taker. There were boxes full of Charles Grimmer\'92s research for articles he would never write. The thought of rummaging through his father\'92s notes had filled Jonathan with guilt, but the thought of leaving his father\'92s work unpublished disturbed him even more. When he finally got around to the task, he found himself ill-suited to the endeavor. He couldn\'92t help but actually 
